column1: 260326;instagram;2018-11-03 18:40:24;FALSE;"i've watched the qspiracy since the start.
steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?
abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa me
column2: a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

column1: the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.
and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

260458;instagram;2018-11-03 21:43:37;FALSE;"""i entered high school with no friends
column2: and i met a guy at the back to school dance. it felt like a cinderella moment
column3: and he asked me out. i was so happy i finally got my first boyfriend. soon after we got together
column4: he started asking me to only hang out with him and his friends. he said my friends caused too much drama
column5: and i agreed. then one day he said i was too clingy
column6: and that's when the physical abuse began.

column1: when it first started i didn't recognize it as abuse
column2: because it was a push here and a slap there
column3: and it never left marks so i thought it wasn't that bad. then once i started having sex with him
column4: he would threaten to cheat on me and make comments about other girls. he said it was normal for a guy to want it
column5: so i dismissed it. that went on for two and a half years until my old friends started noticing the way he treated me and talking to me about it. .

column1: once i finally got the courage to call him out on the abuse
column2: he said he couldn't believe that i didn't love him enough to accept him for who he was
column3: and he dumped me. at first i wanted to get back together with him. i thought that maybe i had overreacted
column4: also it was my junior year of high school and homecoming was soon.

column1: then one night i remembered all the bad things. i thought about the time he broke my tablet because i wouldn't let him have it
column2: and how he broke my flute because band was taking up too much of my time. so i chose not to go back to him
column3: and now i am finally free. i still have ptsd because of the sexual & physical abuse
column4: but i consider myself a victor

column9: judge kavanaugh was found innocent of the alleged sexual assault.

column4: and their rage was reminiscent of the rage that erupted when president trump first entered office. what does this whole circus tell us

column6: and that this new ""guilty until proven innocent"" mindset taken up by the left can do nothing good for western civilization.

column1: 260654;instagram;2018-11-04 03:00:30;FALSE;"tomorrow tara has her 6 weekly review at camhs
column2: and i spent the early morning updating her daily journal. ever since tara started back at school this term i decided to start logging a daily diary of what she gets up to at home
column4: and what her nights look like. with so many different people involved with her
column5: i am constantly getting asked all these questions
column6: and as a exhausted mama i never had the answers. but this log
column7: is mostly negative behaviours and things that have happened each day
column8: and writing it out has taken a huge toll on me emotionally and mentally. so this afternoon when tara went to respite for a few hours i took a break from my uni work
column9: i went and had an undisturbed shower
column10: and i wrote down what i am grateful for today which even doing that little task and having a shower alone changed how i was feeling. i am grateful that after all this time we get respite hours
column11: i am grateful for the house we live in
column12: and i am super grateful for being able to have the time to clean
column13: do some food prep for the week
column14: and put on some of my favourite music. just doing those simple things when tara is here can be a huge challenge
column15: and by taking action  i am changing the way i think
column16: and turning the negative energy into positive energy.

column1: so after my massive brain snap last week it quickly became apparent that i had reached the end of my rope. how did i get here? and what did i learn from this?ü§î that i need to practice what i preach and teach and not be hypocritical!!!üòù. it dawned on me that i had not been for a run or done any exercise for over a week. running is what i call my 'anti depressant 'üòÜ it keeps me level
column2: happier and calmer. with all the chaos of family
column3: work and giving my all to others i didn't give to myself. this ended in a not so happy conversation which thankfully i had the self awareness to admit my part and apologize to the other party. however this was a big slap in the face reminder that i also need to take care of my needs. after a massive weekend standing in 33¬∞ heat driving just over 200km each day round trip
column4: cheering mr 8 on at a touch football carnival i managed a 5km run this afternoon. not that i really felt like it... i was tired... but i had the conversation with kids of what my needs are and what i need from them they were happy to support me. they know happy mum happy life üòÇ but

column1: ive been called 'brave' so many times this last month. a part of me can't understand why. whatever happened
column2: happened close to a decade ago and my family and i did what we had to. i have been called brave for speaking out but i wonder if it's just that.

column1: i can afford to speak out because i am no longer associated with the concerned individual (s) and their behaviour does not reflect on me in anyway. i am unashamed to speak out because i did nothing wrong and the shame is not mine to bear. what then makes me brave
i can't take all the credit for leaving an abusive situation because my family had a big hand in giving me enough perspective to understand that i must.

i cannot take all the credit for fighting it out in court because i had the support of my parents and sister at every single legal consultation and my dad by my side at every court hearing over 4 years.
i cannot claim to have known the right legal approach because i attribute that to my amazing lawyer who fought for me like he would have for his daughter.
for every disappointment we faced at the time
column2: we were blessed with guardian angels in our lives that supported us in more ways than i could ever thank them or their families for.  all in all
column3: i had a rock solid support system that ensured i could get out
column5: heal and re-build a new life at the same time.

column1: it makes me feel like it wasn't just me being 'brave'. and i wasn't just lucky either. it took a village. a whole system of healers and nurturers that held me up
column2: supported my family and me and armed us with the right information
column3: positive vibes and the walk to support their talk.

column1: there are always the ones that secretly enjoy it when you go down. or disappear. these are the times that one learns to filter them out or move them to the generic
